    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-12-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-12-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="77"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d77">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">130 Howe, Audrey Marie</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Canada (<persName type="from">Boal</persName>)
                        to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1158</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ottawa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-12-22">December 22,
                            1932</date>.<lb/>[Received January 3, 1933.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to refer to instruction No. 727
                    of October 7, 1932, concerning the question of the citizenship of Miss Audrey M.
                    Howe and to transmit herewith a copy of a note No. 156 of December the 16th,
                    1932, together with its enclosures, from the Secretary of State for External
                        Affairs,<note n="66" xml:id="d77fn66">Not printed.</note> in which it is
                    stated that the question of oaths to be taken by teachers is a matter within the
                    jurisdiction of the several provinces. The replies of certain of the provinces
                    to an inquiry from the Department of External Affairs are attached
                        herewith.<note n="66" xml:id="d77fn67">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>In the case of Miss Audrey M. Howe, the Lieutenant-Governor of Alberta states
                    that she took the oath of allegiance in 1929. He adds: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Beyond this my Ministers have nothing further to add to the information
                            already furnished.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Pierre de L. Boal</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
